{"info": {"author": "Jo\u00e3o Sampaio", "author_email": "jpmelos@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 1 - Planning", "Environment :: Console", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Topic :: Internet", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP :: Site Management", "Topic :: Software Development", "Topic :: System :: Clustering", "Topic :: System :: Systems Administration"], "description": "=======\nPolygon\n=======\n\n**Polygon is an intelligent infrastructure controller.**\n\nIt automates common procedures of development, testing, provisioning, deployment and maintenance of services and tasks in infrastructures. It has a few core principles and concepts (that can be found in its documentation) for guiding its development, is highly extensible and is designed to be lightweight, running in commodity and high-end bare metals, virtual machines and containers.\n\nRead the detailed conceptualization at http://polygon.readthedocs.io/.\n\n---------------\nGetting started\n---------------\n\nFirst, clone this repository, then build the Docker image::\n\n$ docker build -t polygon .\n\nBuilding the docs\n^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n\n::\n\n$ sudo python run.py builddocs\n\n----------\nDisclaimer\n----------\n\nSo far, this is only a conceptual work. I would love to receive feedback and ideas on this.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": null, "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "http://github.com/jpmelos/polygon", "keywords": "virtualization,clusterization,clusters,distributed systems,infrastructure,containers", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "polygon-infra", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/polygon-infra/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/polygon-infra/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "http://github.com/jpmelos/polygon"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/polygon-infra/0.1a1/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "An intelligent infrastructure controller", "version": "0.1a1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p><strong>Polygon is an intelligent infrastructure controller.</strong></p>\n<p>It automates common procedures of development, testing, provisioning, deployment and maintenance of services and tasks in infrastructures. It has a few core principles and concepts (that can be found in its documentation) for guiding its development, is highly extensible and is designed to be lightweight, running in commodity and high-end bare metals, virtual machines and containers.</p>\n<p>Read the detailed conceptualization at <a href=\"http://polygon.readthedocs.io/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://polygon.readthedocs.io/</a>.</p>\n<div id=\"getting-started\">\n<h2>Getting started</h2>\n<p>First, clone this repository, then build the Docker image:</p>\n<pre>$ docker build -t polygon .\n</pre>\n<div id=\"building-the-docs\">\n<h3>Building the docs</h3>\n<pre>$ sudo python run.py builddocs\n</pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"disclaimer\">\n<h2>Disclaimer</h2>\n<p>So far, this is only a conceptual work. I would love to receive feedback and ideas on this.</p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 2376505, "releases": {"0.1a1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e9e940a00dd4fd1e4fdc87bda8ef1ca4", "sha256": "6647f24b91a7cf2cf19370206e83fabe017ef124cd55d4c0c83c21f262e38752"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "polygon_infra-0.1a1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e9e940a00dd4fd1e4fdc87bda8ef1ca4", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size